<item>
            <title>[SPR-10652] Allow getExtraHiddenFields method of RequestDataValueProcessor to know request method of form</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-10652</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The RequestDataValueProcessor interface is useful for implementing the Synchronizer Token pattern to prevent Cross-Site Request Forgery.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A common usage is to use the getExtraHiddenFields method to add an unpredicatable CSRF token as a hidden input onto every form, which is then verified (perhaps by a HandlerInterceptor) upon submission of the form.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I find that I only wish to apply this to POST requests, as&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a) GET requests should not be state-changing, and therefore are not susceptible to a CSRF attack&lt;br/&gt;
b) Adding the token to a GET request places it on the URL, which is undesirable&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be very convenient if the getExtraHiddenFields method could be used to add a hidden input ONLY to forms which have an action of POST.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks to me like this is called only from the doEndTag method of FormTag. Given that the FormTag seems to know its method, could we have the FormTag either pass that method through to getExtraHiddenFields, or pass the whole FormTag object?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
